

How to Configure the Maven with Nexus:
Create 3 repositories:
Hosted Maven
Snapshot Maven
Proxy Maven
Group Maven (add all the above here)
(Copy their url repectively)

Create user and give full access:
username
password

How to upload now?
S1:
Modify pom.xml with repo location
S2:
modify setting.xml with permission
s3:
mvn deploy

:
Get test project:
wget https://github.com/devops-school/helloworld-java-maven/archive/refs/heads/master.zip

Step 1: (Change the locaiton of the repositories)
<distributionManagement>
    <repository>
        <id>sym</id>
        <name>release softx</name>
        <url>http://13.233.127.211:8081/nexus/content/repositories/broadall/</url>
    </repository>
    <snapshotRepository>
        <id>sym</id>
        <name>snapshot softx</name>
        <url>http://13.233.127.211:8081/nexus/content/repositories/broadall/</url>
    </snapshotRepository>
</distributionManagement>


:Make sure the id is similar

Step 2:
Go to setting.xml
<servers> 
  <server>
  <id>sym</id>
  <username>devops</username>
  <password>password</password>
  </server>
</servers>

